---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="LawBridge | Practical Legal Development">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Practical legal development</p>
        <h1>Build the confidence, skills and direction to move forward in law.</h1>
        <p>
          LawBridge helps aspiring lawyers develop legal knowledge, career confidence,
          practical skills and professional awareness through structured learning,
          mentoring, workshops and resources.
        </p>

        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/students">Start as a Student</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/mentors">Become a Mentor</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dashboard">
        <div class="dots">
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
        </div>

        <div class="dash-top">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">LawBridge Pathway</p>
            <strong>Learn. Practise. Connect. Progress.</strong>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="skill-list">
          <div class="skill-row">
            <div class="skill-top">
              <span>Legal skills</span>
              <small>85%</small>
            </div>
            <div class="bar"><span style="width:85%"></span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="skill-row">
            <div class="skill-top">
              <span>Commercial awareness</span>
              <small>75%</small>
            </div>
            <div class="bar"><span style="width:75%"></span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="skill-row">
            <div class="skill-top">
              <span>Career confidence</span>
              <small>90%</small>
            </div>
            <div class="bar"><span style="width:90%"></span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Why LawBridge exists</p>
        <h2>There is a gap between studying law and feeling ready for the profession.</h2>
        <p>
          Many aspiring lawyers know the theory, but need clearer guidance,
          practical experience, confidence and professional direction.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cards three">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Too much theory</h3>
          <p>
            Students often study legal principles without enough opportunity to
            practise how lawyers think, communicate and solve problems.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Unclear career direction</h3>
          <p>
            It can be difficult to understand pathways, applications, commercial
            awareness and what legal employers actually expect.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Limited support</h3>
          <p>
            Many students need accessible mentoring, structured guidance and
            practical opportunities outside traditional classroom learning.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">The LawBridge method</p>
        <h2>A practical bridge between legal education and legal careers.</h2>
        <p>
          LawBridge is built around four connected stages that help aspiring
          lawyers move from passive learning to confident professional development.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span>01</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Learn</h3>
            <p>Build legal understanding through structured, accessible learning.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <span>02</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Practise</h3>
            <p>Apply skills through workshops, tasks and practical legal scenarios.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <span>03</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Connect</h3>
            <p>Access mentoring, professional insight and supportive legal networks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <span>04</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Progress</h3>
            <p>Develop confidence, clarity and direction for the next career step.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">What LawBridge offers</p>
        <h2>Structured support for every stage of early legal development.</h2>
        <p>
          From first steps into law to building employability confidence,
          LawBridge brings together learning, mentoring and practical experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cards four">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Workshops</h3>
          <p>
            Practical sessions focused on legal skills, applications,
            confidence and professional development.
          </p>
          <a href="/workshops">Explore workshops</a>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Webinars</h3>
          <p>
            Accessible online sessions with insights from legal professionals,
            mentors and career-focused speakers.
          </p>
          <a href="/webinars">View webinars</a>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Mentoring</h3>
          <p>
            Supportive guidance from people who understand the legal journey
            and can help students make informed decisions.
          </p>
          <a href="/mentors">Meet mentors</a>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h3>Resources</h3>
          <p>
            Clear, practical materials to help students understand law,
            applications, commercial awareness and career planning.
          </p>
          <a href="/resources">Browse resources</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
